PLAN OF CARE
We will follow troponins, which are at present mildly elevated; likely partially rate-related.  We will discuss with primary service.  We will proceed with non-ST-MI treatment measures within the guidelines of the primary service's recommendations.  Additionally, we will proceed with FAST HUG and all routine ICU prophylaxis.  Patient will be rate-controlled.  Patient would likely benefit from beta-blockade in this context, as tolerated.

